Class RawSQLWriter

All Implemented Interfaces:
ISQLWriter
public class RawSQLWriter
extends AbstractSQLWriter

Trivial default implementation of ISQLWriter. Expects data records to contain valid SQL statements to perform database writes.
It will attempt to get a string value from each record, and construct a Prepared statement from it.
Potentially quite inefficient as it cannot support reusable prepared statements (obviously)

Since:
3.2.2
Author:
higginse
